[src:batch-vs-streaming/stream-processing] CPUs continue do the job of managing system resources, running applications, and such.
[src:batch-vs-streaming/stream-processing] The stream processor is usually equipped with a fast, efficient, proprietary memory bus (crossbar switches are now common, multi-buses have been employed in the past).
[src:batch-vs-streaming/stream-processing] The exact amount of memory lanes is dependent on the market range.
[src:batch-vs-streaming/stream-processing] As this is written, there are still 64-bit wide interconnections around (entry-level).
